Storyline: The Journey of Identifying and Resolving Technical Debt

In a recent phase of our project lifecycle, the Code Forensic Team conducted a comprehensive analysis of our system and generated two critical documents:

Technical Debt Report
Guidewire Cloud Standard Violation Report

These documents serve as a deep diagnostic view of the system, primarily crafted from a business perspective, ensuring that stakeholders across both technical and non-technical domains can understand the impact and urgency of the findings.

Discovery Phase: Unearthing the Issues
As we explored these documents, we found that they offer a highly detailed breakdown of violations across the application. Each issue is not just listed but precisely located:

The exact file where the violation exists
The specific line number
A clear description explaining the nature of the violation

This level of granularity allows teams to quickly pinpoint problem areas without spending extra effort searching through large codebases.

Understanding the System: Architecture & Flow
To provide better context, the documents also include a well-defined architectural overview of the system.

Flow diagrams illustrate how data and processes move across components
These visuals help teams understand where and why violations may have occurred
They also reveal dependencies and potential ripple effects of each issue

This ensures that fixes are not made in isolation but with a clear understanding of the system’s design.

Structured Insights: Tabular Representation
All identified issues are systematically organized in a tabular format.
This structure makes it easier to:

Review multiple violations at a glance
Compare severity and impact
Prioritize fixes based on business and technical importance

Each row acts like a case file, capturing key details and making tracking straightforward.

Deep Dive: Code-Level Visibility
One of the most powerful features of these reports is their ability to display the exact code snippets where violations occur.
This provides:

Immediate clarity for developers
Reduced time in reproducing or understanding the issue
A direct bridge between analysis and implementation

Instead of abstract descriptions, teams can see the problem exactly as it exists in the code.

Resolution Phase: Guided Remediation
The reports don’t stop at identifying problems—they act as a step-by-step remediation guide.
For each violation, the document provides:

Detailed instructions on how to fix the issue
Visual screenshots for better clarity
Recommended best practices aligned with Guidewire Cloud Standards

This transforms the document from a passive report into an actionable playbook, enabling developers to confidently resolve issues.

Outcome: A Roadmap to Quality and Compliance
Overall, these documents serve as a comprehensive roadmap:

Highlighting existing technical debt
Ensuring alignment with cloud standards
Enabling efficient remediation with minimal ambiguity


